{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:galatians.1",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 1 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:1",
      "text": "Paul, an apostle, not of men, neither by man, but by Jesus Christ and God the Father, who raised him from the dead:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:2",
      "text": "And all the brethren who are with me: to the churches of Galatia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:3",
      "text": "Grace be to you, and peace from God the Father and from our Lord Jesus Christ,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:4",
      "text": "Who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us from this present wicked world, according to the will of God and our Father:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:5",
      "text": "To whom is glory for ever and ever. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:6",
      "text": "I wonder that you are so soon removed from him that called you into the grace of Christ, unto another gospel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:7",
      "text": "Which is not another: only there are some that trouble you and would pervert the gospel of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:8",
      "text": "But though we, or an angel from heaven, preach a gospel to you besides that which we have preached to you, let him be anathema.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:9",
      "text": "As we said before, so now I say again: If any one preach to you a gospel, besides that which you have received, let him be anathema.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:10",
      "text": "For do I now persuade men, or God? Or do I seek to please men? If I yet pleased men, I should not be the servant of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:11",
      "text": "For I give you to understand, brethren, that the gospel which was preached by me is not according to man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:12",
      "text": "For neither did I receive it of man: nor did I learn it but by the revelation of Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:13",
      "text": "For you have heard of my conversation in time past in the Jews' religion: how that, beyond measure, I persecuted the church of God and wasted it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:14",
      "text": "And I made progress in the Jew's religion above many of my equals in my own nation, being more abundantly zealous for the traditions of my fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:15",
      "text": "But when it pleased him who separated me from my mother's womb and called me by his grace,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:16",
      "text": "To reveal his Son in me, that I might preach him among the Gentiles: immediately I condescended not to flesh and blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:17",
      "text": "Neither went I to Jerusalem, to the apostles who were before me: but I went into Arabia, and again I returned to Damascus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:18",
      "text": "Then, after three years, I went to Jerusalem to see Peter: and I tarried with him fifteen days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:19",
      "text": "But other of the apostles I saw none, saving James the brother of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:20",
      "text": "Now the things which I write to you, behold, before God, I lie not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:21",
      "text": "Afterwards, I came into the regions of Syria and Cilicia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:22",
      "text": "And I was unknown by face to the churches of Judea, which were in Christ:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:23",
      "text": "But they had heard only: He, who persecuted us in times past doth now preach the faith which once he impugned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.1.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 1:24",
      "text": "And they glorified God in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
